<tr><td colspan=2><ul>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f98471327574158>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=11&mid=98471327574158>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=11&mid=98471327574158>RE: newbie wizzard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=11&mid=98471327574158#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Mar 15th 10:27 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you wanna be a human, then be that - don't listen to other people telling you that a Erudite or whatever is better.&nbsp;&nbsp;Anyways, as a human, you can start in Freeport (FP) or Qeynos.  I have always started in FP, i don't know Qeynos well.  The FP area is ideal for a newbie, it has the Eastern and Western Commonlands to its west, and the Desert of Ro to the south.  both are good for leveling up fast (the middle of the Desert, the Oasis of Mar, is the best spot in the world for leveling up lvls 12 to 20 or so!).  As a wizard, the casters guild is in West Freeport, the zone you start off in.  Ask around, or download a map at www.eqatlas.com    Then, go to the newbie area at the west gate and kill rats and bats or whatever for a while, its boring but its over fast (like u get lvl 4 in about 5 or 6 hours at most) then go train in Meditate (letting you regain mana faster while your spell book is open) and buy the spells Shock of Fire and Root.  shock of fire is your Direct Damage spell for this level, and Root will hold your opponents in place.  At this level you may not use root that much, and will still fight with your hands rather then spells, but at highest levels Root/Direct Damage (known as "root bombing") is the best way to level up.  (if you do not want to use root just yet, spend the 4gp on an area damage spell (forget name) or gate, which will let you return to your bind spot.  If your not gonna use root, don't spend money on it)  At this point, you can either move to the Desert of Ro, or to the Eastern Commonlands.  after that, just look at websites, get info (as im sure you have been doing while desperately waiting EQ to arrive at your house, hehe), print out maps and such, and go explore!  remember, at the beginning you might not keep the characters you have, but if you research then later you will be able to make high end characters that you want to keep!<br><br>Venorik, lvl 16 Iksar Shaman<br>Darklore, lvl 19 Gnome Necro<br>Cannonfodder, lvl 13 Human Wizard<br>Gnomosaurus, lvl 10 Gnome Wizard</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
